cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with stereo vision and deep convolutional neural networks for disparity map regression. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the need for real-time performance in self-adaptive stereo systems, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm for unsupervised and continuous online adaptation of a deep stereo network. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with deep learning methods for stereo vision. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the development of a new deep stereo architecture.
